The National Student Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS) says students should be vigilant when processing applications and after their financial aid has been approved. This after uncovering fraud and scams in which NSFAS officials have diverted money meant for students to their personal accounts. Three NSFAS employees have been arrested on fraud charges. Executive Administrator of NSFAS Dr. Randall Carolissen says more arrests are expected.  Listen for more: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/755657">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>